cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with point correspondences in images and the existence of fundamental and essential matrices, which are fundamental concepts in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also presents an efficient algorithm using linear algebra, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. The use of linear subspaces and polynomials also suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia), as it deals with image processing and analysis.
